selection sort : it can sorted the values in an ascending order.
there are 5 steps for the elements to sort
step 1 : first we need to find out the minimum value of entire array 
step 2 : after finding we need to sort the elements in order
step 3 : again we find the next minimun and swap 
step 4 : we need to sort until the element is n-2 
step 5 : we dont need to sort the last element which is highest element of entire array.
time complexity : 0(n*2)
beacause it can starts from (n-1)+(n-2)+....+2+1.....
                            = n(n-1)/2
                            =o(n*2)
 code :  public class SelectionSort {

    // Method to perform selection sort
    public static void selectionSort(int[] arr) {
        int n = arr.length;

        // One by one move boundary of unsorted subarray
        for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
            int minIndex = i;

            // Find the minimum element in the unsorted part
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if (arr[j] < arr[minIndex]) {
                    minIndex = j;
                }
            }

            // Swap the found minimum element with the first element
            int temp = arr[minIndex];
            arr[minIndex] = arr[i];
            arr[i] = temp;
        }
    }

    // Main method to test the algorithm
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {64, 25, 12, 22, 11};

        selectionSort(arr);

        System.out.println("Sorted array:");
        for (int num : arr) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }
}
                          
